    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI encountered another such bug when hiding a message window that survived closing the tab.\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: ...rc-dev/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:69: Invalid 'end_col': out of range\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_text'\n\t...rc-dev/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:69: in function ''\n\tvim/_core/editor.lua: in function <vim/_core/editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg = {target = 'msg', timeout = 1000}})\nvim.api.nvim_open_tabpage(0, true, {})\nprint(1)\nvim.defer_fn(function ()\n  vim.cmd.normal('ZQ')\nend, 900)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo such error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-185+g87b5062f94\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
