        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A patch like this seems to make sense to me and prevents the error:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/buffer.c b/src/nvim/buffer.c\nindex 84c555b890..e608f1a25c 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/buffer.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/buffer.c\n@@ -888,6 +888,11 @@ bool buf_freeall(buf_T *buf, int flags)\n     }\n   }\n\n+  // No sense in keeping extmarks when the buffer text is lost and doesn't exist in a file.\n+  if (bt_nofilename(buf)) {\n+    extmark_free_all(buf);\n+  }\n+\n   // Autocommands may have opened another terminal. Block them this time.\n   if (buf->terminal) {\n     block_autocmds();\n```\n\nThough ideally the buffer wouldn't be wiped here and UI2 would still display the message after closing the tabpage (related #21921, #21979).",
            "created_at": "2026-04-15T13:35:02Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39055#issuecomment-4252512647",
